 Eng. Ezaldeen Nasser Saad Albadai
 
-Senior Project Coordinator | Civil Engineer
-Professional CV preview. Use the website CV page print button for the styled PDF layou
-Email: albadai.ezz2003@gmail.com | Phone: +967775196019
+                                                                                                            ‫عزالدين ناصر سعد البداي‬
+
+Civil Engineer & Senior Project Coordinator
+
+                                                                                                ‫مهندس مدني ومنسق مشاريع أول‬
+
+CONTACT
+
+Email: albadai.ezz2003@gmail.com | Phone: +967775196019 | Location: Al-Hodeidah, Yemen | LinkedIn:
+linkedin.com/in/ezaldeen-albadi-02880a356
+
+PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY
+
+Civil Engineer and Senior Project Coordinator with more than 15 years of field experience in designing,
+coordinating, and implementing WASH, water, sanitation, livelihood, clean energy, and infrastructure
+projects in complex humanitarian environments. Strong experience in team leadership, coordination with
+local authorities and communities, budget and project management, technical studies, quantity surveying,
+reporting, and beneficiary-focused implementation.
+
+KEY HIGHLIGHTS
+
+    15+ years of experience.
+    49 water projects.
+    Managed or contributed to projects exceeding 13 million USD.
+    Experience with Islamic Relief, SIDA, IR-USA, IR Canada, IRUSA, WFP-supported activities, and
+    humanitarian field projects in Yemen.
+
+CORE SKILLS
+
+    WASH Projects Management
+    Water Projects
+    Solar Pumping Systems
+    Livelihoods
+    Cash for Work
+    Engineering Supervision
+    Field Team Leadership
+    Community Coordination
+    Beneficiary Reporting
+    Technical Studies and Reports
+    Quantity Surveying
+    Contract Management
+    MS Project
+    AutoCAD
+    Project Coordination
+    Monitoring and Field Documentation
+    Humanitarian Project Implementation
+PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE
+
+1. Project Coordinator - IGNITE Project
+Islamic Relief - Yemen | July 2023 - Present | IR Canada - $3,000,000
+
+    Coordinate project activities with local authorities and communities to ensure community acceptance
+    and organized implementation.
+    Manage water-related projects including solar energy systems, water networks, and operational water
+    tanks.
+    Supervise engineering teams, consultants, and livelihood field teams.
+    Manage small livelihood projects in livestock, agriculture, beekeeping, and entrepreneurship.
+
+2. Project Coordinator - SIDA Project
+Islamic Relief - Yemen | November 2017 - June 2023 | SIDA - $7,000,000
+
+    Supervised the rehabilitation of 49 water projects using solar-powered pumping systems.
+    Managed a team including engineers, consultants, and field assistants across multiple locations.
+    Supervised projects related to health facilities, schools, roads, water tanks, wells, and irrigation
+    channels.
+    Managed 750 small projects and trained beneficiaries on operation and sustainability.
+
+3. Field Officer - ERRY Project
+Islamic Relief - Yemen | July 2016 - November 2017 | IRUSA - $3,352,800
+
+    Supervised 72 diverse projects in water, livelihoods, and services sectors.
+    Managed multiple field teams and monitored implementation quality according to approved plans.
+    Prepared periodic reports supported by meetings and field documentation.
+
+4. Field Officer - IR-USA Project
+Islamic Relief - Yemen | November 2015 - June 2016 | IR-USA - $452,000
+
+    Prepared baseline surveys and identified intervention areas according to needs and priorities.
+    Formed and trained community committees on monitoring and local accountability.
+    Supervised rehabilitation works and field implementation.
+    Ensured documentation of engineering and administrative processes during implementation.
+
+5. Field Monitor - EFA Project
+Islamic Relief - Yemen | August 2015 - October 2015 | WFP
+
+    Managed 10 field assistants and followed up daily distribution plans.
+    Supervised food basket distribution for 10,000 families monthly.
+    Prepared periodic reports for management on progress and challenges.
+
+6. Field Engineer - SNL Project
+Islamic Relief - Yemen | May 2014 - August 2015 | WFP
+
+    Identified water, sanitation, and cash-for-work intervention needs.
+    Managed engineers and supervisors and reviewed implementation quality.
+    Prepared technical and cost studies for 60 projects.
+    Supervised construction and implementation works according to specifications.
+EDUCATION
+
+Bachelor's Degree in Civil Engineering
+Thamar University
+2003
+
+CERTIFICATIONS & TRAINING
+
+    Experience Certificate - 2024
+    Bachelor's Degree in Civil Engineering - 2003
+    ValueLinks Training - 2023
+    Solar Pumping Systems - 2022
+    PMD Pro 1 - 2021
+    Proposal and Report Writing - 2021
+    Microsoft Project - 2024
+    Introduction to Financial Management - 2017
+    Security Focal Point - 2015
+
+LANGUAGES
+
+Arabic - Native
+English - Excellent
 
